Class Meal

  • java.lang.Object
    • ChildCareTech.model.entities.Meal
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    iEntity<Meal,java.lang.Integer>

    @Entity
public class Meal
extends java.lang.Object
implements iEntity<Meal,java.lang.Integer>
    Represents a row of the Meal table saved in the database.

    This class is mapped by Hibernate (basing on JPA annotations) on the Food Meal in the database.

        Create a Meal entity with the provided parameters and id=0.

        Should be used to create a new entity to be saved in the database.

        Parameters:
        canteen - the canteen where this meal is hosted.
        mealNum - the daily number of this meal.
        workDay - the day this meal occurs.
        entryEvent - the meal entrance event.
        exitEvent - the meal exit event.
        status - the meal status.
        menu - the meal's menu.
